parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column lock lever can cause the steering wheel to collapse or become loose, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or collapses
the steering column lock lever falls out of the "locked" position
the steering wheel telescopes inward without warning
the vehicle is difficult to control
and the driver may experience knee injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Fluid Leak/Rack and Pinion Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Power steering fluid is leaking
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
and the vehicle may vibrate or make unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power door lock actuator can cause the doors to become stuck in a locked or unlocked position, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can be a safety concern in emergency situations.
symptoms: The doors will not unlock with the remote key fob or the door-lock switch on the driver's door
the doors must be unlocked manually from inside the vehicle
the doors lock and unlock intermittently
the doors beep several times when trying to unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flickering of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights flicker constantly
the headlights turn off and then back on
the headlights do not shine steadily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system recall can cause various electrical components to malfunction, which can lead to safety issues, such as unintended acceleration or loss of power.
symptoms: None reported
as this is a recall issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy of the odometer can cause safety concerns, such as inaccurate speed readings, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The odometer reading is lower than the actual mileage
the speedometer reading is also inaccurate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause loss of control of the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates briefly after tapping the accelerator pedal
the vehicle strikes an object at a low speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear sunshade can cause reduced visibility through the rear window, which can lead to accidents, particularly at night, in foggy, or rainy conditions.
symptoms: The rear sunshade stays stuck in the up or down position
creates a loud distracting grinding noise when in operation
obstructs the view of the rear road
and reduces visibility through the rear window.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erroneous display of duplicate images on the rear view mirror can cause distraction and confusion while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The rear view mirror displays duplicate images.
